The wc command will display the count of -lines -words -characters or bytes of a file. 

  Syn: $ wc test.txt    
  
Used after a pipeline can be used, for example, to count the number of lines of a specific output. 

  Syn: $ find ~ -name "*.txt" -print | wc -l 
  
Will output the number of .txt files in the HOME directory. 
